{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Navigator","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Preferences","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/SwiftUI","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Input","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Decorations","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/EPUB-Fonts"],"anchor":"Essentials","generated":true}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Highlighting lets users mark up passages in a publication for later reference - a core feature of any reading app. In Readium, highlights are built on top of the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Decoration API"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":". If you want to understand that API in depth or build a custom decoration style, see the "},{"identifier":"Decorations.md","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Highlights"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Readium is only responsible for "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"rendering","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" highlights over the publication content"}]},{"type":"text","text":". Persisting highlights to a database, and any UI around them (color pickers, annotation editors, highlight lists, etc.) are entirely the responsibility of your app. This guide assumes you already have a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Highlight"},{"type":"text","text":" model and a repository to store and observe it."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[!NOTE]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EPUBNavigatorViewController"},{"type":"text","text":" implements "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DecorableNavigator"},{"type":"text","text":" today. Always check if a navigator implements "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DecorableNavigator"},{"type":"text","text":" before enabling decoration-dependent features to future-proof your code."}]}]},{"text":"Setting Up","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Setting-Up"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS shows a context menu when the user selects text in the navigator. You hook into this by declaring a custom "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EditingAction"},{"type":"text","text":" with a selector that will be fired when the user taps the menu item."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let navigator = try EPUBNavigatorViewController(","    publication: publication,","    initialLocation: lastReadLocation,","    config: EPUBNavigatorViewController.Configuration(","        editingActions: EditingAction.defaultActions + [","            EditingAction(title: \"Highlight\", action: #selector(highlightSelection))","        ]","    )",")"]},{"text":"Creating a Highlight from a Text Selection","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Creating-a-Highlight-from-a-Text-Selection"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"action","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" selector must be implemented somewhere in the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"responder chain","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" above the navigator — typically in its parent view controller. iOS routes editing actions up the responder chain, so the navigator passes them through without handling them itself."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@objc func highlightSelection() {","    guard let selection = navigator.currentSelection else {","        return","    }","","    let highlight = Highlight(","        bookId: bookId,","        locator: selection.locator,","        text: selection.locator.text.highlight,","        color: .yellow","    )","","    Task {","        try await highlightRepository.add(highlight)","        \/\/ If you use a reactive pattern (see below), the navigator","        \/\/ updates automatically when the database changes.","    }","","    \/\/ dismisses the text selection handles immediately after saving;","    \/\/ without it, the selection would linger on screen alongside the","    \/\/ newly rendered highlight decoration.","    navigator.clearSelection()","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"navigator.currentSelection","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" returns a ","type":"text"},{"code":"Selection","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" value with:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"locator"},{"type":"text","text":" — a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Locator"},{"type":"text","text":" pointing at the selected range; "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"locator.text.highlight"},{"type":"text","text":" contains the selected string."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"frame","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — the bounding rect of the selection in navigator view coordinates, useful for anchoring a popover.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"text":"Displaying Highlights","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Displaying-Highlights"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rather than calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"apply"},{"text":" manually after each add, delete, or color change, subscribe to your database and re-apply the complete list of decorations whenever it changes. This means there is a single code path for keeping the navigator in sync — no risk of forgetting to update the UI for one of the operations.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The navigator diffs each new list against the previous one internally, so passing the full list every time is both safe and efficient — you never need to track individual changes yourself."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["func observeHighlightDecorations() {","    guard let navigator = navigator as? DecorableNavigator else { return }","","    \/\/ Register the tap callback once (see \"Handling Taps\" below)","    navigator.observeDecorationInteractions(inGroup: \"highlights\") { [weak self] event in","        self?.activateDecoration(event)","    }","","    \/\/ Re-apply on every database change.","    highlightRepository.highlights(for: bookId)","        .receive(on: DispatchQueue.main)","        .sink { _ in } receiveValue: { [weak self] highlights in","            guard let self else { return }","","            let decorations = highlights.map { highlight in","                Decoration(","                    \/\/ Use your database primary key as the highlight's `id` — this is what","                    \/\/ links the `Decoration` back to your model when the user later taps it.","                    id: highlight.id,","                    locator: highlight.locator,","                    style: .highlight(tint: highlight.color)","                )","            }","","            navigator.apply(decorations: decorations, in: \"highlights\")","        }","        .store(in: &subscriptions)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"receive(on: DispatchQueue.main)"},{"type":"text","text":" is required because "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"apply(decorations:in:)"},{"type":"text","text":" updates the UI and must run on the main thread, while database publishers typically deliver on a background thread."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"observeHighlightDecorations()"},{"type":"text","text":" once in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"viewDidLoad"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Handling Taps","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Handling-Taps"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"code":"observeDecorationInteractions(inGroup:onActivated:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to react when the user taps a highlight. Your callback receives "},{"code":"OnDecorationActivatedEvent","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" objects."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"event.decoration.id","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"text":" matches the id you set when building the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Decoration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", so you can use it directly to retrieve the full record from your database.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"code":"event.rect","type":"codeVoice"}]},{"type":"text","text":" gives you the position of the tapped highlight in the navigator view, which you can use to anchor a popover precisely over it."}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["private func activateDecoration(_ event: OnDecorationActivatedEvent) {","    \/\/ Matches the id you used when building the Decoration.","    let highlightId = event.decoration.id","","    Task { @MainActor in","        guard let highlight = try? await highlightRepository.highlight(forId: highlightId) else {","            return","        }","","        presentHighlightMenu(for: highlight, anchoredTo: event.rect)","    }","}","","private func presentHighlightMenu(for highlight: Highlight, anchoredTo rect: CGRect?) {","    let alert = UIAlertController(title: \"Highlight\", message: nil, preferredStyle: .actionSheet)","","    \/\/ Delete: remove from the database; the reactive stream clears the decoration automatically.","    alert.addAction(UIAlertAction(title: \"Delete\", style: .destructive) { [weak self] _ in","        guard let self else { return }","        Task { try await self.highlightRepository.remove(highlight.id) }","    })","","    alert.addAction(UIAlertAction(title: \"Cancel\", style: .cancel))","","    if let popover = alert.popoverPresentationController {","        popover.sourceView = view","        popover.sourceRect = rect ?? view.bounds","    }","","    present(alert, animated: true)","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because the navigator is wired to the reactive stream, updating or deleting a highlight in the database is automatically reflected in the navigator — no extra calls needed."}]},{"text":"Navigating to a Highlight","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Navigating-to-a-Highlight"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"navigator.go(to:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to jump to a saved highlight’s location:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["await navigator.go(to: highlight.locator)"]},{"text":"Complete Example","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Complete-Example"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following self-contained ","type":"text"},{"code":"EPUBReaderViewController","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" wires up the full highlights workflow. ","type":"text"},{"code":"HighlightRepository","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is left as a protocol so the example is storage-agnostic.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["import Combine","import ReadiumNavigator","import ReadiumShared","import UIKit","","\/\/ MARK: - Data model","","struct Highlight {","    \/\/\/ Database primary key (used as Decoration.id)","    var id: String          ","    var bookId: String","    var locator: Locator","    var color: UIColor","}","","\/\/ MARK: - Storage protocol (implement with GRDB, CoreData, etc.)","","protocol HighlightRepository {","    func highlights(for bookId: String) -> AnyPublisher<[Highlight], Never>","    func highlight(forId id: String) async throws -> Highlight?","    func add(_ highlight: Highlight) async throws","    func remove(_ id: String) async throws","}","","\/\/ MARK: - Reader view controller","","class EPUBReaderViewController: UIViewController {","","    private let navigator: EPUBNavigatorViewController","    private let highlightRepository: HighlightRepository","    private let bookId: String","    private var subscriptions = Set<AnyCancellable>()","","    private let highlightDecorationGroup = \"highlights\"","","    init(","        publication: Publication,","        bookId: String,","        lastLocation: Locator?,","        highlightRepository: HighlightRepository","    ) throws {","        self.bookId = bookId","        self.highlightRepository = highlightRepository","","        navigator = try EPUBNavigatorViewController(","            publication: publication,","            initialLocation: lastLocation,","            config: EPUBNavigatorViewController.Configuration(","                editingActions: EditingAction.defaultActions + [","                    EditingAction(title: \"Highlight\", action: #selector(highlightSelection))","                ]","            )","        )","","        super.init(nibName: nil, bundle: nil)","    }","","    @available(*, unavailable)","    required init?(coder: NSCoder) { fatalError() }","","    override func viewDidLoad() {","        super.viewDidLoad()","","        \/\/ Embed the navigator","        addChild(navigator)","        navigator.view.frame = view.bounds","        navigator.view.autoresizingMask = [.flexibleWidth, .flexibleHeight]","        view.addSubview(navigator.view)","        navigator.didMove(toParent: self)","","        \/\/ Wire up highlights","        observeHighlightDecorations()","    }","","    \/\/ MARK: - Displaying highlights","","    private func observeHighlightDecorations() {","        guard let decorator = navigator as? DecorableNavigator else { return }","","        decorator.observeDecorationInteractions(inGroup: highlightDecorationGroup) { [weak self] event in","            self?.activateDecoration(event)","        }","","        highlightRepository.highlights(for: bookId)","            .receive(on: DispatchQueue.main)","            .sink { _ in } receiveValue: { [weak self] highlights in","                guard let self else { return }","                let decorations = highlights.map { h in","                    Decoration(","                        id: h.id,","                        locator: h.locator,","                        style: .highlight(tint: h.color)","                    )","                }","                decorator.apply(decorations: decorations, in: self.highlightDecorationGroup)","            }","            .store(in: &subscriptions)","    }","","    \/\/ MARK: - Creating highlights","","    @objc func highlightSelection() {","        guard let selection = navigator.currentSelection else { return }","","        let highlight = Highlight(","            id: UUID().uuidString,","            bookId: bookId,","            locator: selection.locator,","            color: .yellow","        )","","        Task {","            try await highlightRepository.add(highlight)","        }","","        navigator.clearSelection()","    }","","    \/\/ MARK: - Tapping existing highlights","","    private func activateDecoration(_ event: OnDecorationActivatedEvent) {","        let highlightId = event.decoration.id","","        Task {","            guard let highlight = try? await highlightRepository.highlight(forId: highlightId) else { return }","            await MainActor.run {","                presentHighlightMenu(for: highlight, anchoredTo: event.rect)","            }","        }","    }","","    private func presentHighlightMenu(for highlight: Highlight, anchoredTo rect: CGRect?) {","        let alert = UIAlertController(title: \"Highlight\", message: nil, preferredStyle: .actionSheet)","","        alert.addAction(UIAlertAction(title: \"Delete\", style: .destructive) { [weak self] _ in","            guard let self else { return }","            Task { try await self.highlightRepository.remove(highlight.id) }","        })","","        alert.addAction(UIAlertAction(title: \"Cancel\", style: .cancel))","","        if let popover = alert.popoverPresentationController {","            popover.sourceView = view","            popover.sourceRect = rect ?? view.bounds","            popover.permittedArrowDirections = .down","        }","","        present(alert, animated: true)","    }","}"]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Implementing Highlights"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium","doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/NavigatorOverview"]]},"references":{"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Readium Swift Toolkit is a toolkit for ebooks, audiobooks, and comics written in Swift & Kotlin."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium","title":"Readium","kind":"article","role":"collection","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/readium"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/EPUB-Fonts":{"type":"topic","title":"Font families in the EPUB navigator","kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/EPUB-Fonts","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Readium allows users to customize the font family used to render a reflowable EPUB, by changing the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"Preferences.md","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/epub-fonts"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Navigator":{"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/navigator","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Navigator","kind":"article","role":"article","title":"Navigator","abstract":[{"text":"You can use a Readium Navigator to present the publication to the user. The ","type":"text"},{"code":"Navigator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" renders resources on the screen and offers APIs and user interactions for navigating the contents.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Input":{"title":"Observing user input","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Input","type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/input","abstract":[{"text":"In visual publications like EPUB or PDF, users can interact with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"VisualNavigator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance using gestures, a keyboard, a mouse, a pencil, or a trackpad. When the publication does not override user input events, you may want to intercept them to trigger actions in your user interface. For example, you can turn pages or toggle the navigation bar on taps, or open a bookmarks screen when pressing the Command-Shift-D hotkey.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/NavigatorOverview":{"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/navigatoroverview","title":"Navigator Overview","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about the architecture, configuration, and usage of the Readium Navigator."}],"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/NavigatorOverview"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Preferences":{"title":"Configuring the Navigator","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/preferences","abstract":[{"text":"Take a look at the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","type":"reference"},{"text":" if you are already using the legacy EPUB settings.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Preferences","type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/swiftui/uiviewrepresentable":{"title":"UIViewRepresentable","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewRepresentable"}],"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","type":"link"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/Decorations":{"type":"topic","title":"Decorations","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/Decorations","url":"\/documentation\/readium\/decorations","kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"The Decoration API lets you overlay visual elements on publication content – highlights, search result markers, TTS playback indicators, page-number labels in the margin, and more. For the common case of implementing user highlights, see the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"Highlights.md","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"article"},"doc://Readium/documentation/Readium/SwiftUI":{"url":"\/documentation\/readium\/swiftui","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"The Navigator is built with UIKit and provides ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewController"},{"text":" implementations. Nevertheless, you can integrate them into a SwiftUI view hierarchy using Apple’s ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swiftui\/uiviewrepresentable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Readium\/documentation\/Readium\/SwiftUI","kind":"article","title":"Integrating the Navigator with SwiftUI"},"Preferences.md":{"title":"EPUB navigator preferences","identifier":"Preferences.md","url":"Preferences.md","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"EPUB navigator preferences"}],"type":"link"},"Highlights.md":{"title":"Highlighting guide","identifier":"Highlights.md","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Highlighting guide"}],"url":"Highlights.md","type":"link"},"../Migration%20Guide.md":{"title":"migration guide","identifier":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","url":"..\/Migration%20Guide.md","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"migration guide"}],"type":"link"}}}